.TH hundidero "txt" "TTY" "Mounting Documentation" "Installation Manual"
.SH NAME
El Cañón del Hundidero \- installation instructions
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I El Cañón del Hundidero
(1983) is a work of TTY art composed entirely of ASCII characters,
originally produced on UNIX v7.
It is an original work by
.B Arthur U. Martinel
(b. 1954, Scotland; Instituto de Grafos Textilares, Generation of 1977).
These files are the work.
.PP
The digital version is unique.
Prints derived from it are not editions and carry no numbering.
The source file
.I hundidero.txt
is the original.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B hundidero.txt
The original work.
.TP
.B hundidero.pdf
The file to be printed.
.TP
.B HUNDIDERO.1
These mounting instructions.
.SH PRINT OUTPUT
The artwork is typeset from its source file using the following command:
.PP
.nf
.ft C
(printf '.ft C\\n.ps 7\\n.vs 8\\n.nf\\n'; \\
    sed 's/^\\./\\\\&&/' hundidero.txt) | \\
    groff \-Tpdf \-P\-pa4 \-ms > hundidero.pdf
.ft R
.fi
.PP
Print the resulting PDF file at 100% scale, no fit\-to\-page.
.SH MATERIALS
.TP
.B Printed original
Cotton paper, heavyweight.
One copy per exhibition.
This is the mounted work.
.TP
.B Photocopies
Photocopied from the printed original.
No further specification is required or intended.
.SH MOUNTING
The work is mounted unframed, pinned directly to the wall with four pins,
one at each corner.
No mat, no glass, no frame.
.PP
Pin placement flush with the paper edge.
The paper hangs flat against the wall.
No standoffs.
Wall surface: white or off\-white, matte.
The work reads as a document on a wall, not as an object.
.SH PRINT STACK
A stack of photocopied pages is placed on the floor directly below the
mounted work, flush with the wall.
.PP
The pages are photocopies of the original print.
They are not additional prints from the source file.
All photocopies must be made from the same single original print.
Do not recopy from copies.
Toner fade and copy artifacts are desirable.
.PP
The stack begins the exhibition at
.B 4,646 pages.
This figure corresponds exactly to the total character count of
.I hundidero.txt
(4,646 characters).
Reduced quantities for practical purposes: 464, 46, or 4 pages.
.PP
Pages are not replaced during the exhibition.
Depletion is part of the work.
Pages may be taken by visitors at the discretion of the institution.
.PP
At the close of the exhibition, the printed original is destroyed.
Only the photocopies survive.
.bp
.SH TERMINAL DISPLAY
If exhibited on a period\-correct UNIX terminal, the work should be
displayed as follows:
.PP
.nf
.ft C
$ cat hundidero.txt
.ft R
.fi
.PP
The prompt should be as minimal as possible.
No other content, process, or interface element should be visible on the screen.
.SH SCALING
The work is designed for A4.
The ISO\ 216 proportional series (each size half the area of the previous)
is intentional: the same source file scales to A3, A2, or A1 by adjusting
the groff point size.
The linear scale factor from A4 to A1 is
.if t \(sr8\ \(~~
2.83.
.PP
Suggested values for A1 output:
.PP
.nf
.ft C
(printf '.ft C\\n.ps 20\\n.vs 22\\n.nf\\n'; \\
    sed 's/^\\./\\\\&&/' hundidero.txt) | \\
    groff \-Tpdf \-P\-pa1 \-ms > hundidero_a1.pdf
.ft R
.fi
.SH GENERATING THIS DOCUMENT
.nf
.ft C
groff \-Tpdf \-k \-man HUNDIDERO.1 > hundidero_installation.pdf
.ft R
.fi
.SH AUTHOR
Arthur U. Martinel
